aboutpara: The Glenelg Competitive Programming Team is a coding organization founded by and for high school students interested in competitive programming ficsally sponsored by the Hack Club Foundation which is a 501(c)(3) organization. We have competed and placed first in presitigious competitions such as Lockheed Martin CodeQuest. Our mission is not just to code well, but more importantly to have fun while doing so.
